NEXT STEPS FOR HOORAY HEALTH MEC
1. Review Documents - Read through the required documents for setting up your MEC plan.

Complete the Documents - Complete the Group Set up form. This form will auto-populate the majority of the employer specifics fields within

Review Documents:
Outlined below are the required documents to complete and a quick summary of what is contained within the document. All documents are available for review at hoorayhealth.co/mec.
Administrative Services Agreement (ASA)
The ASA is three party agreement between an employer group, the Third Party Administrator (TPA), and Hooray Health for the MEC plan.
Summary Plan Description (Spd)
The SPD is the Plan Document established by the employer group for the benefit of the eligible employees and outlines the purpose and details of the Plan.
Mec Banking Documents
The MEC Banking Documents are used to provide WebTPA with the designated banking account that the MEC Claims Liability will be paid from.

Only one bank account can be placed on file.
Online Employer Access Form
The online employer access form is used to identify the individuals authorized by the employer group to have access to weekly MEC claim reporting within the WebTPA system. Up to three authorized individuals. 
Summary Of Benefits Coverage (Sbc)
The SBC is an abridged version of the SPD that outlines what is covered under the MEC plan and is to be provided to employees enrolled for coverage.
Complete, Sign & Submit Documents Visit hoorayhealth.co/mec, scroll to the bottom of the page and click "Start Now" to complete the required documents. An 88-page digital document that includes all the agreements and forms will be displayed but don't be alarmed, once the 1-page "Group Set Up Form" at the beginning of the document is completed, most remaining sections of the document will auto-populate. There will be 8 sections for signatures and the bank form at the end must be completed. Once signed and submitted, Hooray Health will execute within 5 business days and a follow up email will be sent to provide any next steps that may be required.

What Is The Cost Of A Retail Clinic Or Urgent Care Center Visit?
A member will pay a $25 copay for a visit to a Retail Clinic or Urgent Care Center that is in the Hooray Health Network. The member will not receive a balance bill or additional charges for covered procedures at in-network providers.*
How Can I Tell If A Provider Is In The Hooray Health Network?
Providers can be found using the "Provider Look-Up" feature on the Hooray Health App or by searching at myhoorayhealth.com/providers.
Are Hooray Health Plans considered comprehensive health insurance plans? 
No. Hooray Health Plans are categorized as fixed indemnity insurance plans. The plan pays a predetermined amount on an annual basis, regardless of the total charges incurred. The accident insurance reimbursed medical expenses solely in connection with accidental injuries.
Is There A Deductible?
Hooray Health Plans do not have a deductible that you have to meet before your benefits start.
Can I Use My Primary Care Physician (Pcp) With Hooray Health Plans?
Yes, however, you may see a cost-saving when visiting a provider in the First Health Network. The First Health Providers have contracted rates which means lower rates than an out of network provider.
Can I Change My Plan During The Plan Year?
You may only make a change to your plan or coverage level during the plan year if you have a Qualified Life Event (QLE). 
Qle - What Is It And How To Submit?
A Qualified Life Event is an event such as a marriage, death, birth of a child, or loss of coverage elsewhere that would allow a member to change coverage in the middle of the plan year. Proof of a QLE can be submitted through the Member Portal under Upload Document to Hooray Health.
How Does Billing Work?

If your employer deducts the premium through payroll (list bill), payments will be automatically deducted based on your payroll cycle. If you are paying by credit card (direct pay), the first month's benefit coverage is paid for on the day you enroll. After the initial payment, payments are scheduled on the 15th each month and pay for the following month coverage.
What is the cost of a Telemedicine visit? 
Hooray Health has an unlimited Telemedicine service available to members 24/7/365 and has a $0 consult fee every time. Members can speak to a physician at their convenience, and if needed, their prescriptions can be called into a pharmacy of their choice.

 If In-Network Provider Issues Occur
